As a Swarm Architect, I'll craft the raw XML for fragment_chat.xml with the[3D[K
the specified design requirements.

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    android:id="@+id/root_layout"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical">

    <LinearLayout
        android:id="@+id/header_layout"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
        android:background="#000080"  <!-- Transparent Navy Background -->
        android:gravity="center_vertical"
        android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
        android:orientation="horizontal">

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/app_icon"
            android:layout_width="24dp"
            android:layout_height="24dp"
            android:src="@mipmap/ic_launcher" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/app_name"
            android:layout_width="0dp"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:textColor="#ffffff"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            app:layout_constraintStart_toEndOf="@id/app_icon"
            android:layout_marginHorizontal="8dp" />

    </LinearLayout>

    <ScrollView
        android:id="@+id/chat_scrollview"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="0dp"
        android:layout_weight="1"
        android:scrollbars="none"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@id/header_layout">

        <LinearLayout
            android:id="@+id/chat_container"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:paddingHorizontal="16dp">

            <!-- Messages will be inflated here -->
        </LinearLayout>

    </ScrollView>

</LinearLayout>
```

Now, let's create the gold-etched message bubble layout.

```xml
<!-- Message Bubble Layout -->
<LinearLayout
    android:id="@+id/message_bubble_layout"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:orientation="vertical">

    <View
        android:id="@+id/border_top"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="1dp"
        android:background="#ffd700" />  <!-- Gold Border -->

    <LinearLayout
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:orientation="vertical">

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/message_text"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textColor="#000000"  <!-- Black Text -->
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:paddingHorizontal="8dp"
            android:paddingVertical="4dp" />

        <View
            android:id="@+id/border_bottom"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="1dp"
            android:background="#ffd700" />  <!-- Gold Border -->

    </LinearLayout>

    <View
        android:id="@+id/border_left"
        android:layout_width="4dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="#ffd700" />  <!-- Gold Border -->
    <View
        android:id="@+id/border_right"
        android:layout_width="4dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="#ffd700" />  <!-- Gold Border -->

</LinearLayout>
```

You can now use these layouts to create your chat UI with a transparent nav[3D[K
navy background and gold-etched message bubbles.

